data.meta_description: 472 likes, 9 comments - woodbridge.todd on June 20, 2024: "In medieval times Sandwich was a main Kent and UK port, it was and still is, a principal Cinque Port. Before the River Stour silted up, the river was wide and deep enough for great sailing ships. The name of the town is, most likely, Saxon in origin, approximately meaning sandy place, or the place on the sand. #england #history #tourist #medieval #town #sandwich #worthavisit".
